**Difference between dot and bracket notation
Answer:Dot Notation:
/We use dot notation when you already know the exact property name. It is simple and easy to read.
Example: student.name
Bracket notation ([])
We use bracket notation when the property name is not fixed or is stored in a variable. It is also used if the property name has spaces or special characters.
Example: student["name"]


